#### 1.2.4 Body Page Branding

| Element | Branding Rule |
|---------|--------------|
| Section headings (H1) | `primary_colour` text; bottom border rule in `primary_colour`, 4pt, spanning text width only (not full page — achieved via paragraph border, not a table) |
| Sub-headings (H2) | `secondary_colour` text, no border |
| Sub-sub-headings (H3) | `secondary_colour` or `accent_colour` text, italic, no border |
| Primary table headers | `primary_colour` background, white bold text |
| Secondary table headers | `secondary_colour` or `#555555` (dark grey) background, white text |
| Table alternating rows | White and `accent_colour` (very light tint) or white and `#F7F7F7` (near-white grey) |
| Table borders | 1pt `#CCCCCC` (light grey) — never black borders |
| Callout boxes | Left-border or full-border in `primary_colour`; fill in `accent_colour` at 15–20% opacity or a fixed very-light tint; title text in `secondary_colour`, bold |
| Advice Summary box header row | `primary_colour` background, white text |
| Chronology table header | `primary_colour` background, white text |
| Score/status indicators (H/M/L) | Fixed traffic-light: H = `#C8E6C9` (green), M = `#FFF9C4` (amber), L = `#FFCDD2` (red) — these are not branded, they are semantic |
| Bullet points | Body font, no colour decoration |
| Bold inline text | `#212121` (near black) — never primary colour for inline bold |
| Sign-off block top border | `primary_colour`, 2pt |
| Footer rule | Light grey or `primary_colour`, 1pt |

> **Critical rule for the report builder:** All colour and font references in the report assembly code must be resolved from the account branding config at render time. They must **never** be hardcoded. This allows any survey firm to apply their own brand without a code change.

