#### 1.2.5 Logo Handling Rules

1. Store as **PNG with transparent background** (preferred) or SVG. A white/reversed version may be stored separately for use on dark backgrounds.
2. Never stretch the logo — always scale proportionally.
3. **Cover page:** Display at `firm_logo_width_px` (configured in account settings). Positioned bottom left.
4. **Running header:** Computed automatically as 30–35% of `firm_logo_width_px`. Positioned inline left within the header paragraph, not in a table cell.
5. **If no logo is configured:** Render the firm name in the heading font at the equivalent size.
6. **If the cover background behind the logo is dark** (e.g. primary_colour band): use the reversed/white logo variant if stored, otherwise ensure the logo zone has a white or light background.

---

#### 1.2.6 Cover Page vs Body: What Changes

| Element | Cover Page | Body Pages (2+) |
|---------|-----------|-----------------|
| Logo position | Bottom left, full size | Top left in header, ~33% size |
| Header bar | None | Logo + title text + rule |
| Background | White with coloured bands | White |
| Vessel name | Large, in `primary_colour` band | Not repeated |
| Report status | Prominent badge | In header text (abbreviated) |
| Page number | None | In footer |

> **Note for report builder:** The cover page is rendered separately from the body page loop. Body pages all use the same header/footer template. The cover page is page 1; the AI Declaration + Advice Summary is page 2; section content begins page 3.

