## 3. AI Processing Requirements

### 3.1 API Configuration

- **Provider:** Anthropic Messages API (private, closed API — not claude.ai)
- **Model:** Must be explicitly pinned per call — never resolved from an alias
  - Example: `claude-sonnet-4-6-20251001`
- **Zero data retention:** Anthropic standard API terms — prompts and responses are transient
- **DPA:** A Data Processing Agreement with Anthropic must be executed before live deployment

### 3.2 AI Use Cases in Report Builder

| Report Section | AI Function | Human Review Required |
|----------------|-------------|----------------------|
| Background | Draft narrative from surveyor field notes / voice transcript | Yes — surveyor confirms attribution |
| Damage Description | Structure and draft from field notes, organise by system | Yes — surveyor verifies each item |
| Cause Consideration | Draft technical analysis from surveyor's notes | Yes — surveyor edits and confirms opinion |
| Advice Summary | Auto-populate from case data; draft editable text fields | Yes — surveyor reviews before export |
| Surveyor's Notes | Optional drafting assistance | Yes |
| Document Vault | Extract structured data from uploaded source documents (invoices, reports) | Yes — surveyor confirms extracted data |

### 3.3 AI Audit Log Schema

Every AI API call must write a record to `ai_generation_log`:

```sql
CREATE TABLE ai_generation_log (
  log_id            UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  case_id           UUID REFERENCES cases(case_id),
  report_section_id TEXT NOT NULL,        -- e.g. 'background', 'damage_description'
  model_version     TEXT NOT NULL,        -- e.g. 'claude-sonnet-4-6-20251001' — PINNED, never alias
  source_doc_ids    TEXT[],              -- Array of Document Vault IDs used as context
  prompt_hash       TEXT NOT NULL,        -- SHA-256 of the full prompt
  prompt_text       TEXT NOT NULL,        -- Full prompt (stored for auditability)
  ai_output_text    TEXT NOT NULL,        -- Raw AI response
  surveyor_review   TEXT,                -- 'reviewed_accepted' | 'reviewed_amended' | 'surveyor_authored'
  reviewer_user_id  UUID,
  reviewed_at       TIMESTAMP,
  created_at        TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### 3.4 AI Audit Record Annexure

At report export time, the platform auto-generates **Annexure I — AI Audit Record** from the `ai_generation_log` for the case. It contains:

- One row per section where AI was engaged
- Columns: Report Section | AI Function | Model & Version | Source Documents | Surveyor Review Action
- Signed by the attending surveyor at finalisation (signature block appended)
- This annexure is **locked** at sign-off and cannot be edited post-export

### 3.5 AI Disclosure Paragraph

At export time, the platform inserts an auto-generated disclosure paragraph on Page 2 of the report (after legal designations, before the Advice Summary). The paragraph:

- Identifies the AI system used by name
- Lists the report sections where AI was engaged (from audit log)
- States that all content was reviewed and confirmed by the signing surveyor
- References the AI Audit Record annexure
- Is **locked** on signing and cannot be edited post-export

Sections where `surveyor_review = 'surveyor_authored'` are excluded from the sections list in the disclosure paragraph.

If **no AI was used** in the report (all sections surveyor-authored), the disclosure paragraph is suppressed and Annexure I is omitted.

