## 4. Report Builder — Section Assembly Rules

The report builder assembles the case record into a structured document. The rules below apply to both docx and PDF output.

### 4.1 Section Order

Pages assemble in this order:

1. **Cover Page** (always)
2. **Page 2:** Legal Designations → AI Declaration (if applicable) → Advice Summary
3. **Table of Contents**
4. **Section 1:** Introduction / Scope of Work
5. **Section 2:** Attending Representatives
6. **Section 3:** Vessel's Particulars
7. **Section 4:** Machinery / Equipment Particulars *(include only if `casualty_type` = machinery-related)*
8. **Section 5:** Class & Statutory Certification
9. **Section 6:** Available Information Sources
10. **Section 7:** Chronology of Events
11. **Section 8:** Background
12. **Section 9:** Damage Description
13. **Section 10:** Cause Consideration
14. **Section 11:** Repairs
15. **Section 12:** General Services & Access *(optional — include if `general_services` array is non-empty)*
16. **Section 13:** Repair Costs
17. **Section 14:** Repair Times
18. **Section 15:** Surveyor's Notes *(include only if non-empty)*
19. **Section 16:** Documents Retained on File
20. **Section 17:** Documents Requested
21. **Section 18:** Principal Dates
22. **Section 19:** Waiver *(always — use account `default_waiver_text`)*
23. **Sign-off Block** (attending + reviewing surveyor, date)
24. **Liability Disclaimer** *(always — use account `default_disclaimer_text`)*
25. **Annexure A:** Assessment of Repair Costs
26. **Annexure B:** Repair Invoices
27. **Annexure C:** Survey Certificate(s)
28. **Annexure D:** Incident / Insurance Claim Report
29. **Annexure E:** Photographs (with photo register index)
30. **Annexure F:** Third-party Reports
31. **Annexure G:** Chronological Correspondence
32. **Annexure H:** Prior Reports (if supplementary/final)
33. **Annexure I:** AI Audit Record *(include only if AI was used)*

### 4.2 Cover Page Assembly Rules

- Logo: from `account.firm_logo`, centred, at configured display width
- Title band: background = `account.primary_colour`; text white
- Report status banner: derived from `case.report_status` — styled prominently (bold, coloured)
- Info box (2-column):
  - LEFT: "Occurrence: [date] — [nature of casualty]"
  - RIGHT: "Claim's Reference: [claim_reference]" / "Technical File No.: [technical_file_no]" / "Report No.: [report_version]"
- Cover photo: sourced from Document Vault, tagged `cover_photo = true`. If none tagged, section is omitted (no placeholder shown)
- Footer: `account.firm_name` | phone | email | website — small text

### 4.3 Chronology Table Format

The Chronology of Events must render as a **table**, never as narrative prose:

| Date | Time | Movement / Event |
|------|------|-----------------|

- Header row: `account.primary_colour` background, white text
- Rows: alternating white / `account.accent_colour` or light grey
- Date format: DD/MM/YYYY
- Time format: HHMM (24h)
- Events sorted ascending by date/time

### 4.4 Attending Representatives Table

Three-column table: Name | Company | Function/Role

Additional note for remote contacts: append "(by telephone)" or "(by correspondence)" to the Function field.

### 4.5 Causation — Mandatory Separation

The report builder must enforce that the three cause sub-sections are clearly labelled and separated:

- **11.1 Owner's Allegation** — must open with: *"The following cause of loss has been alleged by [source]:"* or *"No formal written allegation of cause has been made at the time of this report."*
- **11.2 Technical Analysis** — must open with: *"In the opinion of the Undersigned..."* (or equivalent)
- **11.3 Remediation Actions**

The builder must **refuse to export** a Final Report if `owner_allegation_text` and `surveyor_opinion_text` are identical strings (copy-paste without separation).

### 4.6 Cost Table Format

The cost section must render as a formal accounts table:

| Item | Description | Invoice Ref. | Amount | Allocation |
|------|-------------|--------------|--------|-----------|

Followed by a summary:

| | |
|-|-|
| **Total — Claim Items** | $X,XXX.XX |
| **Total — Owner's Account** | $X,XXX.XX |
| **Total — Subject to Adjustment** | $X,XXX.XX |
| **GRAND TOTAL** | $X,XXX.XX |

All amounts must include the currency code from `cost_currency`.

The summary must be followed by: *"The above costs are approved/noted without prejudice to Underwriters' rights and without admission of liability."*

### 4.7 Without Prejudice Notation

The builder must insert a `WITHOUT PREJUDICE` notation:
1. At the top of Page 2 (before Advice Summary)
2. Immediately below the cost summary table
3. In the Waiver section

### 4.8 Photo Register

Annexure E must open with a **photo register** — a thumbnail index:

| Photo No. | Location / Component | Direction / Context | Date | Significance |
|-----------|---------------------|---------------------|------|-------------|

Thumbnails at ~120px wide. Full-size captioned photos follow after the register.

Caption format: `[Photo N] — [component/location] — [direction/context] — [date] — [significance to claim]`

### 4.9 Report Version Numbering

- Each new report generated for a case increments `report_version`: R001, R002, R003, etc.
- The report header and Advice Summary must both display the version number
- A Final Report must state: *"This report supersedes all prior survey reports for this casualty for the purposes of the survey record. All prior reports are incorporated by reference."*
- A Progress or Supplementary report must state: *"This report supplements Report [prior version] dated [date] and does not supersede it."*

### 4.10 Sign-off Block

Two-column layout:

```
ATTENDING SURVEYOR          |  REVIEWED BY
--------------------------- | ---------------------------
[Full Name]                 |  [Full Name]
[Qualifications]            |  [Qualifications]
[Role / Title]              |  [Role / Title]
[Company]                   |  [Company]
[Location]                  |  [Location]
Date: ___________           |  Date: ___________
```

Both columns must be signed digitally or by wet signature before the report is exported as Final.

The builder must **block Final Report export** unless both `signed_off_attending` and `signed_off_reviewing` are true.

