## 5. Data Input Front End — Requirements

### 5.1 General Principles

- **Mobile / tablet first:** Surveyors complete most data entry in the field, often on an iPad. The UI must be optimised for touch interaction and offline capability.
- **Section-by-section workflow:** The input UI should mirror the report section structure. The surveyor moves through sections in order but can return to earlier sections at any time.
- **Field-level AI assistance:** AI drafting is available per section (field notes → narrative), triggered explicitly by the surveyor — never automatic.
- **Voice input:** The platform should support voice transcription for narrative fields (Background, Damage Description, Cause, Surveyor's Notes). Transcript is fed to AI for structuring, surveyor reviews.
- **Offline mode:** Core data entry must work offline. Sync to cloud when connection is restored.
- **Progress tracking:** Visual indicator showing which sections are complete, in progress, or empty.

### 5.2 Screen / Flow Map

```
Case List
  └── New Case / Open Case
        ├── Case Header (report status, references, instructing party)
        ├── Vessel Particulars
        ├── Machinery Particulars (conditional on casualty type)
        ├── Class & Statutory Certification
        ├── Attending Representatives
        ├── Document Vault (upload source docs)
        │     └── AI Data Extraction (per uploaded document)
        ├── Available Information Sources (auto-populated from Vault + manual)
        ├── Chronology of Events
        │     └── Add Event (date / time / description)
        ├── Background
        │     ├── Field notes input (text / voice)
        │     └── AI Draft → Review → Confirm
        ├── Damage Description
        │     ├── Add Damage Item (system → location → nature → extent → photos)
        │     └── AI Draft Narrative → Review → Confirm
        ├── Cause Consideration
        │     ├── Owner Allegation (text input, source field)
        │     ├── Technical Analysis (text / voice / AI draft)
        │     └── Remediation Actions (text / voice / AI draft)
        ├── Repairs
        │     └── Add Repair Item (type → description → dates → approvals)
        ├── General Services & Access (checklist)
        ├── Repair Costs
        │     ├── Add Cost Line Item (description → amount → allocation → invoice ref)
        │     └── Cost Summary (computed totals)
        ├── Repair Times
        ├── Surveyor's Notes
        ├── Documents Retained on File (auto-populated from Vault + manual)
        ├── Documents Requested
        ├── Principal Dates (milestone log)
        ├── Advice Summary (auto-populated, editable)
        ├── Photo Manager (organise, caption, set cover photo)
        └── Export
              ├── Preview Report
              ├── AI Audit Record review
              ├── Sign-off (attending + reviewing)
              └── Export as .docx / PDF
```

### 5.3 Document Vault

The Document Vault is the central repository for all source documents attached to a case:

| Field | Type |
|-------|------|
| `vault_id` | UUID |
| `case_id` | FK |
| `file_name` | string |
| `file_type` | enum: `PDF` \| `Image` \| `DOCX` \| `XLSX` \| `Other` |
| `document_category` | enum: `Incident Report` \| `Invoice` \| `Survey Certificate` \| `Logbook` \| `Diver Report` \| `Investigation Report` \| `Correspondence` \| `Photograph` \| `Other` |
| `is_cover_photo` | bool | If true, used on cover page |
| `annexure_assignment` | enum: `A` through `I` \| `None` | Which annexure this document belongs to |
| `uploaded_at` | timestamp |
| `ai_extracted` | bool | Whether AI data extraction has been run on this doc |
| `ai_extracted_data` | JSON | Structured data extracted by AI (e.g. cost line items from invoice) |
| `surveyor_confirmed` | bool | Surveyor has reviewed AI extraction |

### 5.4 Key Validation Rules (Export Gate)

The system must prevent export of specific report types unless these conditions are met:

| Rule | Applies To |
|------|-----------|
| All mandatory sections completed (non-empty) | All report types |
| Owner allegation text ≠ surveyor opinion text | Final, Interim |
| Both sign-off records confirmed | Final only |
| Cost total > 0 or explicitly marked "costs TBD" | Final only |
| AI audit log entries have `surveyor_review` set | All reports where AI was used |
| Advice Summary reviewed and confirmed | All report types |

