## 6. Report Format Output — docx vs PDF

### 6.1 Current State

The current implementation outputs **`.docx`** using the Anthropic API + document assembly code. This is a valid and deliverable format for most H&M underwriters who expect Word documents for annotation and claims file management.

### 6.2 Target State — Flutter PDF Module

The target Flutter module will support **native PDF output** in addition to docx. The PDF renderer should:

- Reproduce all styling (fonts, colours, tables, logos) from the account branding config
- Embed fonts (Arial or configured font) to ensure consistent rendering across devices
- Support page numbering in format: `Page N of Total`
- Support photo embedding at consistent DPI
- Support digital signature fields in the sign-off block
- Lock the document against editing post-export (PDF/A or similar)

### 6.3 Shared Data Model

Both docx and PDF output consume the **same case data model** (Section 2). The output renderer is the only layer that differs. This means:

- All business logic (section assembly rules, validation, causation separation, WP notation) lives in the platform layer, not the renderer
- Switching from docx to PDF output requires only a renderer swap, not a data model change
- AI audit log, disclosure paragraph, and annexure structure apply identically to both formats

### 6.4 Intermediate Milestone: Clean docx Output

Before the Flutter PDF module is built, the docx output must be brought to production quality:

- [ ] Account branding applied (logo, colours, fonts) — not hardcoded
- [ ] All 25 sections + annexures A–I supported
- [ ] Chronology rendered as a table (not prose)
- [ ] `WITHOUT PREJUDICE` notation in all four required locations: footer (every page), Page 2 formal designation, cost summary at each approval, and Waiver section
- [ ] Photo register in Annexure E
- [ ] AI Audit Record in Annexure I (auto-generated from audit log)
- [ ] AI disclosure paragraph auto-generated and locked on export
- [ ] Sign-off block with dual-signature gate
- [ ] Report version numbering (R001, R002, etc.)
- [ ] Report status banner on cover page
- [ ] cantSplit on table rows to prevent header/content separation at page breaks

