## 7. Successive Reporting Rules

The platform enforces the following report sequence logic:

| Report Type | Can Create If | Previous Report Required |
|-------------|--------------|--------------------------|
| Preliminary (R001) | Case opened, date of attendance set | None |
| Progress (R002+) | At least one prior report exists | Yes — reference prior version |
| Interim | At least one prior report exists; milestone defined | Yes |
| Supplementary | At least one prior report exists; new material info documented | Yes |
| Final | All mandatory sections complete; both sign-offs confirmed | At least one prior report |

Rules for the report builder:
- **Preliminary report:** Exports with `[PRELIMINARY — SUBJECT TO REVISION]` banner. All cost figures annotated as estimates.
- **Progress report:** Header states: *"This report supplements Report [R00N] dated [date]."* Only changed sections need to be complete; unchanged sections carry forward with a reference note.
- **Final report:** States that it supersedes all prior reports. Locks the case record after export.
- **Supplementary report:** Explicitly documents what new information was received and how it changes earlier findings.

