## 8. Compliance & Legal Requirements

### 8.1 GPN-AI Compliance (Federal Court of Australia, April 2026)

The following platform behaviours are required for GPN-AI compliance:

- [ ] AI model version pinned and stored per API call
- [ ] Full prompt text stored per API call in `ai_generation_log`
- [ ] AI output stored per API call in `ai_generation_log`
- [ ] Surveyor review action stored per section (reviewed_accepted / reviewed_amended / surveyor_authored)
- [ ] AI disclosure paragraph auto-generated from audit log at export time
- [ ] Disclosure paragraph locked post-signing (cannot be edited)
- [ ] AI Audit Record annexure locked post-signing
- [ ] Platform does not use consumer AI interfaces — API only
- [ ] No confidential case data transmitted to publicly accessible AI systems

### 8.2 Professional Standards

- The attending surveyor's professional opinions must be explicitly attributed to the surveyor, not to the AI
- The platform must not allow AI-generated text to appear in the report without surveyor review confirmation
- The sign-off block must include a declaration: *"I confirm that the professional opinions and technical findings in this report are my own and that all AI-assisted content has been reviewed and confirmed by me."*

### 8.3 Without Prejudice Protocol

"Without Prejudice" serves different legal functions depending on where it appears in the report. There are **four distinct placement locations**, each with a separate purpose. All four are required.

| Location | Purpose | Form |
|----------|---------|------|
| **Page footer — every page** | Passive notice ensuring no extracted page can be read as an unqualified statement. Established practice in Marsh Maritime and other Australian H&M formats. | Short line: *"This report is supplied without prejudice to any or all parties involved."* Combined with confidentiality notice in footer. |
| **Page 2 — formal designation** | The primary, prominent WP declaration. Appears before the Advice Summary, immediately after legal designations. Makes clear that the entire report — including all cost approvals that follow — is issued without prejudice. | Standalone bold line: *"WITHOUT PREJUDICE"* followed by a sentence of explanation. |
| **Cost summary — at each approval** | The operationally critical WP notation. Applied to each section of the cost account as it is approved, preserving underwriters' right to contest coverage while permitting repairs to proceed. Failure to apply WP here is the most legally dangerous omission. | Inline at each approved section: *"The above costs are approved without prejudice to Underwriters' rights and without admission of liability."* |
| **Waiver section** | The closing WP statement, confirming that no acts of the Undersigned or Underwriters in attending the vessel, approving repairs, or preparing the report shall constitute a waiver or acceptance of liability. | Full waiver paragraph — see Section 4.1, item 20. |

**Implementation rules:**

- All four locations must be present in every report that approves any costs. Preliminary reports with no cost approvals still require the footer, Page 2, and Waiver placements.
- The footer WP line is **not** a substitute for the Page 2 designation or cost approval notations — it is an additional passive reminder.
- All cost line items must have `cost_without_prejudice = true` before export is permitted.
- The builder must log a warning and block export if any approved cost items lack the WP flag.
- The score of M (partial) given to Marsh Maritime in the format analysis reflects the fact that their footer carries a partial WP notice but WP notation is absent from the cost approval sections — a gap the platform must close.

