**Logo rendering rules:**
- Always scale proportionally — never stretch or distort
- PNG with transparent background is the preferred format; SVG also accepted
- A reversed/white variant may be stored separately for use on dark `primary_colour` backgrounds
- The header paragraph must be tall enough to show the logo unclipped — do not use nested table structures that crop the image
- If no logo is configured: render `firm_name` in `heading_font` at the equivalent size

### 9.3 Cover Page Template Note

The cover page follows the Oceanomatics technical report template as the reference design (as seen in technical project reports produced by Oceanomatics). This template style applies to the **cover page only** — the running header, footer, and all body page elements follow the H&M report best practice standard established in the format analysis, independent of the cover page design.

Key adaptations for H&M use on the cover page:

- The **client reference block** (top left) shows the underwriter's name and claim reference — not the vessel owner's logo
- A **report status badge** (PRELIMINARY / FINAL etc.) must be added — mandatory for H&M, not present in the technical report template
- The **bottom info box** (two-column) adds Occurrence, Claim Reference, File No., and Report Version No.
- The **vessel name** appears in the large title band
- The **Oceanoservices logo** is anchored bottom left on the cover page

### 9.4 Default Theme (Oceanoservices)

For the Oceanoservices account specifically:

```
primary_colour:    #3D1A6E   (deep corporate purple)
secondary_colour:  #6A3D9A   (mid purple)
accent_colour:     #F0ECF7   (very light lavender)
body_font:         Arial
heading_font:      Arial
firm_logo:         oceanoservices_logo.png (transparent background)
firm_logo_width_px: 300
```

The cover page title band uses `primary_colour`; the report type band uses `secondary_colour`. Body page headers, section headings, and table headers all follow the branding rules in Section 1.2.

### 9.5 Theming Architecture Requirement

- Branding config must be stored as a **named theme** in the account settings
- A survey firm can define multiple themes (e.g. one for H&M reports, one for P&I reports, one for technical/engineering reports)
- The theme is selected at case creation and stored on the case record
- The report builder resolves **all** colour and font references from the selected theme at render time
- Hardcoded colours anywhere in the report assembly code are a **defect** — every colour must trace back to a theme config field
- The cover page template layout (zone positions, band structure) is fixed by the platform; only the colours, logo, and content fields are variable

